    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-02-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-02-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="649"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d649">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">357.AB/2–452</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Secretary of State</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian"
                            type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1952-02-04">February 4,
                            1952</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">White House Dictation</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">Item No. 2</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">Kashmir—Dr. <persName corresp="#p_GDF1">Graham</persName>
                </p>
                <p>I discussed the importance of Dr. <persName corresp="#p_GDF1">Graham</persName>’s
                    making another effort in India to settle the Kashmir dispute. The President
                    approves of his going and has sent him word to that effect.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
